ASP.NET Core Web API (.NET 8 / .NET 6 / .NET Core 3.1 – as applicable)
Used to build RESTful backend services with high performance and scalability.

C# (Latest Version)
Primary programming language for business logic and API implementation.

Entity Framework Core
Used for database access, ORM mapping, and data persistence with MS SQL Server.

JWT (JSON Web Token) Authentication
Implemented for secure token-based authentication and authorization.

Windows Authentication (if applicable)
Used for internal user authentication within enterprise environments.

Role-Based Authorization
Ensures controlled access to APIs based on user roles and permissions.

ASP.NET Core Middleware Pipeline
Used for request handling, authentication, logging, and exception management.

Swagger / OpenAPI
Used for API documentation, testing, and contract validation.

Dependency Injection (Built-in DI Container)
Enables loose coupling, improved testability, and maintainable code.

LINQ
Used for querying and manipulating data efficiently.

Configuration Management (appsettings.json)
Environment-specific configuration handling.
-------

Database Technology Stack – Microsoft SQL Server

Microsoft SQL Server (2019 / 2022 – as applicable)
Used as the primary relational database for storing application data securely and reliably.

Stored Procedures
Implemented for complex business logic, improved performance, and enhanced security.

Indexes and Constraints
Used to ensure data integrity, enforce relationships, and optimize query performance.

Joins, Views, and Functions
Used for efficient data retrieval and reporting requirements.

Transaction Management
Ensures data consistency and reliability during insert, update, and delete operations.

Data Security
Role-based access, schema-level permissions, and secure connections are enforced.

Backup and Recovery
Supports regular database backups and disaster recovery mechanisms.

Integration with Entity Framework Core / ADO.NET
Used for seamless interaction between the application and the database layer.



